\lim_{x\to 0} \frac{\sin x(1 - \cos x)}{x^2}
\lim_{x \to 0} \frac{\sin x}{x}=1.
\lim_{x \to 0} \frac{1-\cos x}{x^2} = \lim_{x \to 0} \frac{(1-\cos x)(1+\cos x)}{x^2 (1+\cos x)}=\lim_{x \to 0} \frac{\sin^2 x}{x^2(1+\cos x)},
\lim_{x \to 0} \frac{1-\cos x}{x^2}=\lim_{x \to 0} \left( \frac{\sin x}{x} \right)^2 \times\lim_{x \to 0}\frac{1}{1+\cos x}=\frac{1}{2}.
\lim_{x \to 0} \frac{\sin x (1-\cos x)}{x^2}=\lim_{x \to 0} \sin x \times \lim_{x \to 0} \frac{1-\cos x}{x^2}=0 \times \frac{1}{2}=0.
f=\frac{\sin(x)(1-\cos(x))}{x^2}=\frac{g(x)}{h(x)}
L=\lim_{x\to 0}f=\lim_{x\to 0}\frac{g'(x)}{h'(x)}
L=lim_{x\to 0}\frac{\cos(x)-\cos(x)^2+\sin(x)^2}{2x}
L=\lim_{x\to 0}\frac{\sin(x)(4\cos(x)-1)}{2}=0
